DynIntervalTree<T>
public final class DynIntervalTreeImpl<T>
extends AbstractDynIntervalTree<T>

DynIntervalTreeImpl implements the interval tree for fast searching of intervals in a given time range. An interval tree is a red-black tree that maintains a dynamic set of elements, with each node DynNode containing an interval DynInterval. The leaf nodes do not contain data, and reference to a dummy sentinel node (nil). The root is also a nil sentinel node, whose left reference points to the network root. DynIntervalTreeImpl guarantees O(log n) insertion and deletion of elements.
